Today, the last day of Chanukah, is called ‘Zot Chanukah’, based on the words of the Torah reading that is read today (Numbers 7:84 – ‘Zot’, ‘This’ was the dedication of the altar). According to tradition this day is so powerful that each of us, every man and woman, has the ability and power to change for the good, whatever was decreed on Rosh HaShana and sealed on Yom Kippur... this day, the last day of Chanukah is (secretly) the last day of the High Holy Days! The holy Arizal and students of the Baal Shem Tov revealed that today, Zot Chanukah, it is within our reach to merit abundance of blessing and success in every area of our lives, physical and spiritual. Even the simple person’s prayer is accepted in Heaven today as if that person was a perfect tsaddik. Whoever spends time today in prayer and personal prayer, such as reciting Psalms and begging Hashem for our needs with a contrite and honest heart, will see miracles. Just ask Hashem for what is missing, and thank Him for what you have! All the light of Chanukah is revealed today! Every prayer and blessing is within reach!
